{
  "name": "Locus: Hush Stone",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature. The properties of this item are affixed to a wonderous item.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>This locus was previously in the possession of Hormuz the Ensorcellite of the Fallen Queen. It was affixed to his face cover.</p><p>While attuned, the Hush Stone magically merges with a <strong>wonderous item</strong> of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, and requires 10 minutes to complete.  Upon completion, the item radiates a localized field that causes the item to make no sound when it makes contact with other objects. Once completed, if applied to a weapon it becomes magical for the purpose of overcoming resistances.</p><p><strong>Effect: </strong>When the attuned casts a spell, they can spend a charge to cast it without any verba<span class=\"No-Break\">l components. Furthermore, when you expend a charge on a spell that requires a creature to hear you, the save DC is increased by the number of charges missing. You have a number of charges equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all expended charges at Dawn.</span></p>",
